 brooks member of the us house of representatives from new yorks th district in office march   – march   preceded by william kirkpatrick succeeded by john m bowers joel thompson personal details born august   salisbury connecticut died march   aged  niagara falls new york resting place oakwood cemetery political party democraticrepublican whig spouses letitia breckinridge relations augustus porter brother children peter augustus porter elizabeth lewis porter parents joshua porter abigail buell profession politician lawyer awards congressional gold medal military service allegiance  united states of america  new york servicebranch new york state militia years of service  rank major general battleswars war of   • battle of black rock  • battle of chippewa  • battle of niagara  • siege of fort erie peter buell porter august   – march   was an american lawyer soldier and politician who served as united states secretary of war from  to  contents  early life  career  united states congress  war of   new york politics and return to congress  secretary of war  personal life  descendants  legacy  references early lifeedit peter buell porter was born on august   one of six children born to dr joshua porter – and abigail buell – who married in  in lebanon connecticut his siblings were joshua porter – abigail porter – eunice porter – augustus porter – sally porter – his father dr joshua porter a  graduate of yale fought in the revolutionary war as a colonel he was at the head of his regiment in october  when john burgoyne surrendered his  men after the battles of saratoga after the war he was elected to various official positions for fortyeight consecutive years his maternal grandparents were peter and martha buell née grant of coventry connecticut he attended and graduated from yale college in  studied law in litchfield connecticut with judge tapping reeve who also taught aaron burr and john c calhoun careeredit in  porter was admitted to the bar and commenced practice in canandaigua new york from  to  he was clerk of ontario county and was a member of the new york state assembly ontario and steuben co in  in the fall of  porter moved to black rock new york later part of buffalo and became a member of the firm of porter barton  company with his brother augustus which controlled transportation on the niagara river the company portaged goods by land from lake erie to lewiston on the niagara river through niagara falls then shipped them east on lake ontario united states congressedit in  he was elected to the united states house of representatives as a democraticrepublican he served in the th and th united states congresses holding office from march   to march   during his service in congress he was a leading figure among congressional war hawks and chairman of the committee that recommended preparation for war with great britain and was known as an early supporter of james madison porter along with henry clay and others pressured madison to end the discussion and take up arms against england in what became known as the war of  at the same time from  to  he was a member of the erie canal commission a commission on inland navigation established in  by the new york state legislature to survey a canal route from the hudson river to the great lakes porter served on the commission with fellow democraticrepublicans simeon de witt and dewitt clinton the federalists on the committee were gouverneur morris william north thomas eddy and stephen van rensselaer in  porter and the democraticrepublicans were joined by robert r livingston and robert fulton charles d cooper joined in  war of edit while in congress porter realizing the level of america’s unpreparedness for war pushed for greater numbers of soldiers and supplies when his efforts fell on deaf ears he instead offered his experience in trade to the military beginning in may  he was served as assistant quartermaster general in the new york state militia as a brigadier general he participated in and criticized general alexander smyth’s abortive operations against british canada in  at the battle of black rock culminating in a bloodless duel between the two the historian john r elting wrote of the duel stating unfortunately both missed porter later raised and commanded a brigade of new york militia that incorporated a six nations indian contingent and led his command with distinction he brokered a deal with red jacket who agreed to provide  troops under porters command for his actions he was presented a gold medal under joint resolution of congress dated november   for gallantry and good conduct during the battle of chippewa the battle of niagara and the siege of fort erie with the end of military operations porter went to washington where he was given command of all american forces on the niagara frontier by president madison when news of a peace treaty arrived he returned to civilian life and was declared a hero by his fellow citizens new york politics and return to congressedit from february  to february  he served as secretary of state of new york as a democraticrepublican under new york governor daniel d tompkins he was also elected to the th united states congress although his term in congress began on march   the actual session began only in december and he took his seat on december   on january   he resigned having been appointed a commissioner under the treaty of ghent which caused a controversy as to the constitutionality of sitting in congress and holding this commissionership at the same time in  his political friends of tammany hall printed ballots with his name and distributed them among their followers to vote for porter for governor of new york at the special election which was held after the resignation of governor daniel d tompkins dewitt clinton the otherwise unopposed candidate was fiercely hated by the tammany organization and porter received about  votes although he was not really running for the office porter became a regent of the university of the state of new york in  and served in that capacity until  he was again a member of the state assembly erie co in  but vacated his seat when he was appointed to the cabinet secretary of waredit from may   to march   porter served as us secretary of war under president john quincy adams and was an advocate for the removal of eastern indians beyond the mississippi he moved to niagara falls in  and was a presidential elector on the whig ticket in  personal lifeedit in  porter married letitia breckinridge – the daughter of john breckinridge – a us senator from kentucky from  to  and attorney general of the united states under jefferson from  to  her mother was mary hopkins cabell of the cabell political family letitia was widowed from her first marriage in  to alfred william grayson who had died in  grayson a graduate of cambridge university was the son of senator william grayson of virginia through her first marriage she had a son john breckinridge grayson – together peter and letitia had peter augustus porter – who married mary cabell breckenridge – elizabeth lewis porter – who was rumored to have almost married millard fillmore who later served as president of the united states from  to  on march   general porter died in niagara falls and was interred in oakwood cemetery along with brother augustus descendantsedit a paddlesteamer named the general porter was launched in  his son peter a porter died in the bloody battle of cold harbor during the american civil war his grandson was peter augustus porter – a us representative from new york and his nephews were augustus seymour porter a united states senator from michigan and peter b porter jr an assemblyman and speaker of the new york state assembly legacyedit fort porter porter avenue in buffalo porter road in niagara falls and porter township in niagara county are all named in honor of gen porter porters letters and papers survive in the library collections of the buffalo history museum in  a paddle steamer named the general porter was launched on lake erie she sailed out of buffalo new york until  when she was sold to the royal navy which renamed her the hms toronto the royal navy employed her patrolling lake erie the st clair river and the upper niagara river referencesedit notes  a b c d e f g h bell william gardner  march  peter buell porter historyarmymil center of military history united states army retrieved  october    a b c welles albert  history of the buell family in england from the remotest times ascertainable from our ancient histories and in america from town parish church and family records illustrated with portraits and coat armorial new york society library retrieved  october    the late col porter funeral of col pa porter sketch of his life and character the new york times  june  retrieved  october    foran jack the day they turned the falls on the invention of the universal electrical power system librarybuffaloedu university of buffalo retrieved  october    a b c d ridler jason  war of  wwweighteentwelveca rcgshdiparks canada retrieved  october    morris north de witt eddy porter and cooper ceased to be commissioners when the legislature appointed a new commission consisting of clinton van rensselaer ellicott holley and young  bernstein peter l   koeppel gerard   elting john r  amateurs to arms a military history of the war of  algonquin books of chapel hill p  isbn    grande dr joseph a lachiusa chuck peter b porter wwwbuffaloahcom the courierexpress buffalo architecture and history retrieved  october    google book abridgment of the debates of congress from  to  page   a b breckinridge john – biographical information bioguidecongressgov retrieved on october    index to politicians breckinridge the political graveyard retrieved on october    the cabells and their kin a  – alexander brown – google books booksgooglecom july   retrieved on october    elizabeth lewis porter  oakwood cemetery wwwacsubuffaloedu oakwood cemetery inc retrieved  october