 highest honors in  from the university of north carolina at chapel hill where he was a moreheadcain scholar a national merit scholar a member of phi beta kappa a marshall scholarelect a reserve wide receiver on the varsity football team and a finalist in the  campuswide slamdunk competition henry received his phd in economics from the massachusetts institute of technology mit in  while in graduate school he served as a consultant to the governors of the bank of jamaica and the eastern caribbean central bank eccb his research at the eccb contributed to the intellectual foundation for establishing the first securities exchange in the eastern caribbean currency area careeredit academicedit peter blair henry is dean of new york university’s leonard n stern school of business the youngest person to hold the position he assumed the deanship in january  and joined the nyu stern faculty as the william r berkley professor of economics and finance henry joined nyu stern from stanford university where he was the konosuke matsushita professor of international economics the john and cynthia fry gunn faculty scholar and associate director of the center for global business and the economy at the stanford university graduate school of business henry’s research and teaching have received support from the national science foundation’s early career development program  from  to  henry was a national fellow at the hoover institution henry also serves as a member of the board of directors at the national bureau of economic research nber the nation’s leading nonprofit nonpartisan economic research organization as a member of the council on foreign relations as a nonresident senior fellow of the brookings institution as a member of the federal reserve bank of new yorks economic advisory panel and as a member of the board of directors for citi in  henry was awarded the foreign policy association medal the highest honor bestowed by the organization governmentedit an expert on the global economy henry led the external economics advisory group for thensenator barack obama’s presidential campaign in  following the historic victory on november  henry was chosen to lead the presidential transition team’s review of international lending agencies such as the international monetary fund imf and the world bank in june  president obama appointed him to the president’s commission on white house fellowships books publications and mediaedit henry’s first book turnaround third world lessons for first world growth basic books march  directly addresses issues of economic efficiency as well as matters of international relations in it henry argues that the secret to emerging countries’ success and to the future prosperity of the developed world as well is discipline—a sustained commitment to a pragmatic growth strategy in many ways turnaround is an extension of henry’s very first lesson in international economics which he received at the age of eight as his family moved from the caribbean island of jamaica to affluent wilmette illinois the elusive answer to the question of why the average standard of living can be so different from one country to another still drives him today the author of numerous articles and book chapters henry is best known for a series of publications in the three flagship journals of the american economic association that overturn conventional wisdom on the topics of debt relief international capital flows and the role of institutions in economic growth “debt relief” journal of economic perspectives winter  “capital account liberalization theory evidence and speculation” journal of economic literature december  “institutions vs policies a tale of two islands” american economic review may  henry’s writing also appears in global crises global solutions the published proceedings of the copenhagen consensus an international conference on how to make the most efficient use of the world’s scarcest resources the economist magazine named the conference publication one of the best business books of  henry is regularly cited in the media including on cnbc financial times foreign policy and others personal lifeedit he lives with his wife and their four sons in new york city he is also the cousin of orange is the new black star samira wiley referencesedit  murray sarah february   the bigger picture financial times retrieved december     peter b henry phd biography fsistanfordedu  retrieved   peter blair henry sternnyuedu  retrieved   board of directors wwwnberorg october  retrieved   officers and directors wwwcfrorg retrieved   peter blair henry wwwbrookingsedu retrieved   economic advisory panel wwwnewyorkfedorg retrieved   peter blair henry wwwciticom retrieved   foreign policy association awards medal to peter henry sternnyuedu february   retrieved   president obama announces appointments to the president’s commission on white house fellowships the white house  office of the press secretary june   retrieved   henry peter b turnaround third world lessons for first world growth basic books march  retrieved   arslanalp serkan and peter b henry debt relief journal of economic perspectives  retrieved   henry peter b capital account liberalization theory evidence and speculation journal of economic literature  retrieved   henry peter b and conrad miller institutions vs policies a tale of two islands american economic review  retrieved   lomborg bjørn global crises global solutions cambridge university press  retrieved   staff books of the year  the economist november   retrieved   stafftaking on emerging markets cnbc february   retrieved   henry peter b the wisdom of the market foreign policy february   retrieved  external linksedit home page nyu stern school of business peter blair henry faculty page nyu stern school of business meet the new dean sternbusiness spring  curriculum vitae of dr peter blair henry stanford university march  roberts russ july   peter henry on growth development and policy econtalk library of 